"title": "5096: Jacob, the patriarch",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5096: jacob, the patriarch",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>God's covenant promises to Abraham were inherited by Jacob, through his father Isaac, and so it was through his line of descent that the promised Messiah was to come.</p>\n<h2>Jacob was one of the three patriarchs</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod3:6\">EXO 3:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num32:11\">NUM 32:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut1:8\">DEU 1:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt8:11\">MAT 8:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt22:32\">MAT 22:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts3:13\">ACT 3:13</a></p>\n<h2>Jacob received the Abrahamic promises</h2>\n<h3>God's promise to Abraham</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen12:1-Gen12:3\">GEN 12:1–12:3</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Jacob chosen in preference to Esau</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom9:11-Rom9:13\">ROM 9:11–9:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen25:23\">GEN 25:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal1:2\">MAL 1:2</a></p>\n<h3>The promises given to Jacob and his descendants</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen28:3-Gen28:4\">GEN 28:3–28:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen28:13-Gen28:15\">GEN 28:13–28:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen35:11-Gen35:12\">GEN 35:11–35:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev26:42\">LEV 26:42</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr16:17\">1CH 16:17</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps105:10\">PSA 105:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb11:9\">HEB 11:9</a></p>\n<h2>Jacob's descendants</h2>\n<h3>He fathered the twelve tribes</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod1:1-Exod1:5\">EXO 1:1–1:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs18:31\">1KI 18:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr2:1-1Chr2:2\">1CH 2:1–2:2</a></p>\n<h3>He was the father of the nation</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps22:23\">PSA 22:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps77:15\">PSA 77:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa45:19\">ISA 45:19</a></p>\n<h2>Jacob as a symbol for the nation</h2>\n<h3>Jacob and Israel were linked together as equivalent terms for the nation</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps14:7\">PSA 14:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num23:7\">NUM 23:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num24:5\">NUM 24:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr16:13\">1CH 16:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps78:5\">PSA 78:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps114:1\">PSA 114:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps135:4\">PSA 135:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa9:8\">ISA 9:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa43:28\">ISA 43:28</a></p>\n<h3>The nation is described as the house of Jacob</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod19:3\">EXO 19:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa2:6\">ISA 2:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa8:17\">ISA 8:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer5:20\">JER 5:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos9:8\">AMO 9:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:33\">LUK 1:33</a></p>\n<h3>Other descriptions of the nation</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut33:4\">DEU 33:4</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps87:2\">PSA 87:2</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa27:9\">ISA 27:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa59:20\">ISA 59:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa41:21\">ISA 41:21</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer30:18\">JER 30:18</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam2:2\">LAM 2:2</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal2:12\">MAL 2:12</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom11:26\">ROM 11:26</a></p>\n<h3>National and patriarchal references merged</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps46:7\">PSA 46:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps20:1\">PSA 20:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps24:6\">PSA 24:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps75:9\">PSA 75:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps94:7\">PSA 94:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps99:4\">PSA 99:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer10:16\">JER 10:16</a></p>",
